{ This study will contain my personal annotations on the famous book by David Bronstein: "Zurich 1953." These games were played in the Zurich 1953 Candidates tournament by the world's best. David Bronstein was one of the competitors. This won't have the same feel as other NoseKnowsAll educational studies, as the annotations will be quite light, but I hope you get something out of it anyway. To get the most out of this study, I strongly suggest you follow along the actual book as well!

Throughout the annotations, Bronstein's words will be put "in quotes," while my personal comments will be plain text. }
 *


