1. d4 (1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Bg7 5. c4 d6 6. Nc3 Nf6 7. Be2 O-O 8. Be3 Nc6 9. O-O Bd7 10. Qd2 Nxd4 11. Bxd4 Bc6 12. f3 a5 13. Rac1 a4 { A line in the accelerated dragon which seemingly "transposes" to the ideas present in this game. }) 1... Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. g3 (3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Nf3 (4. e4 d6 5. h3 O-O 6. Be3 e5 7. d5 Na6 8. g4 { [%cal Gf1e2,Gh3h4,Gh4h5] }) 4... d6 5. e4 O-O 6. h3 (6. Be2 e5 (6... Bg4 7. Be3 e5 8. d5 a5 9. h3 Bxf3 10. Bxf3 Na6) 7. O-O Nc6 8. d5 Ne7 { [%cal Gb2b4] } 9. Ne1 Nd7 10. Be3 f5 11. f3 f4 12. Bf2 g5 { [%cal Gh7h5,Gg5g4] }) 6... e5 7. d5 a5) 3... Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. Nc3 d6 6. Nf3 Nbd7 7. O-O e5 8. e4 Re8 { [%cal Gd4d5] } 9. h3?! { Doesn't directly deal with black's Re8, giving the move purpose. } (9. d5 { [%cal Gf7f5,Ge8f8] }) 9... exd4 10. Nxd4 Nc5 11. Re1 a5 12. Qc2 (12. Ndb5 { The knight can't be kicked out. } { [%csl Gd6][%cal Gb5d6] }) 12... a4 (12... Nfxe4 13. Nxe4 Bxd4 14. Bg5! Qd7 15. Nf6+ Bxf6 16. Bxf6 $16) 13. Be3 c6 14. Rad1 Nfd7 { [%csl Gc5,Ge8][%cal Gg7a1,Gc8h3] } (14... Qa5 { The "old way" of playing } 15. Bf4 { [%cal Gf4d6] } 15... Rd8 (15... Bf8 { Forces black passively backwards. })) 15. f4 (15. g4 Ne5 { [%cal Gd4c6,Ge3c5] } 16. Qe2 a3 17. b3 Qh4 { [%cal Gc3e2] } 18. Qd2 { Computer line }) 15... Qa5 { Kasparov, Garry - Pablo Marin, Alejandro, 1-0, Barcelona sim, 1988, https://lichess.org/xWO7Z1Ap } { [%cal Gg2f3,Ge3f2,Gg1g2] } 16. Bf2 Nb6 17. Bf1 { [%cal Gg1g2] } (17. b3 { [%cal Ga5b4] } 17... axb3 18. axb3 Qb4 19. Rb1) (17. Nb1 Qb4 18. Nd2 h6 { [%csl Gc5,Gb6,Gb4] } 19. a3 Qa5 20. Nb1) 17... Bd7 { [%cal Ga8d8,Gd7c8] } 18. a3!? { [%cal Ge4e5,Gd6d5,Gf7f5,Gg7a1] } 18... Rad8 19. Kh2 Bc8 20. Na2? (20. Kg2 Nbd7 21. g4 $16) 20... Nbd7 21. Bg2 Nf6 22. Nc3 Rd7 23. Nf3 Rde7 24. Ng1 { d6 is never really a weakness } (24. Qd2! Ncxe4?? (24... Kh8 25. e5 dxe5 26. Nxe5 Be6 27. Qd6 { [%cal Gd6c5] } 27... Nfd7 28. g4!) 25. Nxe4! Qxd2 26. Nxf6+ Bxf6 27. Rxd2) (24. Nxa4) 24... Nfd7 25. Bd4 (25. Rxd6 Bxc3 26. bxc3 Nb6 27. Qa2 Nb3 28. Qe2) 25... Nb6 26. Bxg7 Kxg7 27. Rxd6 Nxc4 28. Rdd1 Be6 { [%csl Ga5][%cal Gf7f6,Ge6f7] } 29. Qf2 f6 30. Nf3 Bf7 31. e5! fxe5 32. Nxe5 Nxe5 33. Rxe5 (33. fxe5 Rxe5 34. Rf1 Rf5 35. Qd4+ Kg8 36. Rxf5 gxf5 $10) 33... Rxe5 34. fxe5 Rxe5 35. Rf1 Rf5 (35... Qc7 $10) 36. Qd4+ Kg8 37. Rxf5 gxf5 38. Qe5 { [%cal Gf7g6] } 38... Qb6 (38... Bg6 { forced, but ugly }) 39. Qxf5 Bg6 40. Qe5 Nd3 { [%cal Gb6f2,Gd3e1,Gf2g2] } 41. Qe6+ Kg7 42. Qe7+ (42. Nd5 Qxb2 { White only has a perpetual }) 42... Bf7?? (42... Kg8 43. Nd5 Qc5!! { An engine move that Bronstein and Boleslavsky missed } 44. Nf6+ Kh8 $14) 43. Ne4 Qxb2 44. Nd6 Qf2 45. Ne8+ (45. h4!! { Another engine move that everyone missed. } { [%csl Gh4][%cal Gh2h3,Ge7g5] } 45... h6 (45... Ne1 46. Ne8+!! Kg6 (46... Kg8 47. Nf6+ Kg7 48. Nh5+ Kg8 49. Qd8+ Be8 50. Qxe8+ Qf8 51. Qxe1) 47. Qg5#) 46. Kh3!! b5 (46... Qe1 { [%csl Gf7] } 47. Qxf7+) (46... Kg8 47. Nxf7 Qxf7 48. Qd8+ Kg7 49. Qxd3) 47. Ne8+ Kg8 48. Nf6+ Kg7 49. Nh5+ Kg8 50. Qd8+ Kh7 51. Be4+ $18) 45... Kg8 46. Nf6+ Kg7 47. Nh5+ Kg6 48. g4 Nc5 $10 { Draw agreed. } 49. h4 Ne6 $10 (49... h6?? 50. Qxc5 Qxc5 51. Be4+!! $18) 50. Kh3 Qe3+ 51. Kh2 1/2-1/2


