1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 c5 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 b6 { [%csl Gg2][%cal Gc8b7,Gb7g2] } (6... Nc6 7. Bd3 O-O 8. Ne2 { [%csl Ga5] } 8... b6 (8... d6 9. O-O e5) 9. e4 { [%cal Gc1g5] } 9... Ne8! 10. O-O (10. e5? d6 11. f4 Qh4+ 12. g3 Qe7 13. O-O $15) (10. d5 Ne5) 10... Ba6 11. f4 f5! { The variation I know of. I don't think it existed in the 50s. }) 7. Bd3 Bb7 8. f3 { [%cal Gf3f4,Ge3e4] } 8... Nc6 9. Ne2 O-O 10. O-O Na5 11. e4 { [%cal Gc1g5] } 11... Ne8!? { [%csl Gc4,Gc3,Gd4] } (11... Rc8!? { Computer novelty. The idea is to take on d4 and then take on c4. } 12. e5 Ne8 13. d5 Ba6 14. d6 f6 { But black is on a knife's edge here. }) 12. Ng3 cxd4? { Too early. Rc8 should be played first. } (12... Rc8 13. d5 Nd6 $10) 13. cxd4 Rc8 14. f4? (14. c5! bxc5 15. dxc5 Rxc5 16. Be3 Rc6 17. Bxa7 $16) 14... Nxc4 15. f5 { [%cal Gf5f6,Ge8f6,Gc1g5] } 15... f6 { Hopefully this diagonal doesn't kill black... } (15... b5 16. f6 Nxf6 17. Bg5 Qb6!! 18. Bxf6 gxf6 $19 { [%cal Gb6d4,Gd4f6] }) 16. Rf4 { A human-like attack commences on the kingside. } { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gd1h5,Gf4h4,Gh4h7] } 16... b5 { But black ignores it and counterattacks from the queenside. } { [%csl Gb6,Gd4][%cal Gd8b6] } 17. Rh4 Qb6 { [%cal Gb6d4] } 18. e5 { [%cal Gh4d4] } (18. Ne2? { [%cal Gd1h5] }) (18. Bb1! { My preferred defense of the d pawn } { [%cal Ga1a2,Ga2f2] } 18... e5 { [%csl Gd4] }) (18. Qh5 Qxd4+ 19. Kh1 Qxa1 $19 { [%cal Gh5h7,Ga1c1] }) 18... Nxe5 { [%cal Gb6g1] } 19. fxe6 Nxd3 (19... dxe6 20. Bxh7+ $16) 20. Qxd3 (20. exd7?? Qc6!! { [%csl Gd7][%cal Gc6g2] }) 20... Qxe6 (20... dxe6 21. Qxh7+ { [%csl Gh7] } 21... Kf7 22. Be3 $15) 21. Qxh7+ Kf7 { [%cal Gc1e3,Ge6e3] } 22. Bh6 Rh8!! { [%csl Gc2] } 23. Qxh8 Rc2 { [%cal Gc2g2,Ge6c4,Gg1f1] } 24. Rc1 { [%cal Gc2g2,Gg1f1] } (24. Re4?? Bxe4 25. Nxe4 Qxe4 { [%cal Ge4g2] }) (24. d5!! { [%cal Gh4e4,Gg3e4] } 24... Bxd5 (24... Qb6+ 25. Kh1 Qf2 { [%csl Gg2] } 26. Rg1 Bxd5 27. Re4 $16) (24... Rxg2+ 25. Kxg2 Qxd5+ 26. Re4 f5 27. Qxe8+ $18) (24... Qxd5) 25. Rd1!! Rxg2+ (25... Qb6+?? { [%csl Gd4][%cal Gh4d4,Gd1d4] } 26. Rdd4 $18) 26. Kf1 $10 { [%cal Gd1d5,Ge6b3] }) 24... Rxg2+ 25. Kf1 (25. Kh1 Rxg3+ 26. d5 Bxd5+ 27. Re4 Bxe4#) 25... Qb3!! { [%csl Gd3,Gf3][%cal Gb3f3,Gf3f2,Gg2g1,Gb3d3] } 26. Ke1 (26. Rf4 Qd3+ 27. Ke1 Qe3+ { [%cal Gh6e3] } 28. Kf1 (28. Kd1 Qd2#) 28... Qg1#) 26... Qf3 $19 { [%cal Gf3f2,Gg2g1] } 0-1


