1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Bg5 c5 6. d5 Na6? { Too slow of a plan to reroute to c7 and support a b5 advance. } (6... O-O { [%cal Gf2f3,Gf1d3,Gd1d2] } 7. Qd2 e6 8. Bd3 exd5 9. cxd5 a6 10. a4 Re8 11. Nge2 Nbd7 12. O-O Ne5 $10 { A normal benoni-type game }) 7. Bd3 Nc7 8. Nge2 a6 9. a4 Rb8 10. O-O O-O 11. Qc2?! (11. h3! { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gf6g4,Gc8g4] }) 11... Bd7 (11... Ng4! { [%cal Gg4e5] }) 12. h3 b5 13. f4! { [%csl Gf8,Gf1][%cal Gb5c4,Gd3c4] } (13. axb5 axb5 14. f4! (14. b3 { [%cal Gg7a1] } 14... b4 15. Na4 { [%cal Gf6e4] })) 13... Nfe8 14. axb5 axb5 15. Ra7 bxc4 16. Bxc4 Ra8 17. Rxa8 { [%csl Ge7][%cal Gg5e7] } 17... Nxa8 18. Qb3 f6 19. Bh4 Qb6 20. Qa3 (20. Qa2 Nec7 21. b4!! Qxb4 (21... cxb4+ 22. Bf2 Qb7 23. Rb1 Kh8 24. Qa5 $16 { [%cal Ga5b4] }) 22. Rb1!! { The queen is trapped! }) 20... Nec7 21. b3 (21. b4 cxb4+ 22. Bf2 bxa3 23. Bxb6 $19) 21... Nb5 22. Nxb5 Bxb5 { [%csl Gf1][%cal Gf6f5] } 23. f5 $14 { [%csl Gg7,Ga8] } (23. Be1!? { [%cal Ge1a5,Ge1c3] }) (23. Ra1!? f5? 24. e5! dxe5 { [%cal Gh4e7] } 25. d6+ { [%cal Gb5c4] } 25... Kh8 26. dxe7) 23... Bh6 (23... Kh8 24. Nf4 { The threat! } 24... g5 25. Ne6 gxh4 26. Nxf8 Bxf8 27. Qxa8) 24. fxg6 hxg6 25. e5! Bxc4 26. bxc4 dxe5 27. Qd3 { [%csl Gf6,Ge5,Bc5,Be7][%cal Gd5d6,Ge2c3,Gf1b1] } (27. Bf2 Rc8 28. Qd3 Kg7 29. h4 { Bronstein's line which keeps the most control over the position and avoids the trades that Najdorf finds in the game. }) 27... Kh7 28. Nc3 Qb3 (28... Nc7 { Needed, but black's position is slowly crumbling due to his lack of activity. }) 29. Rb1 e4! { [%cal Gb3d3,Gd3e4,Gb3c3] } 30. Rxb3 exd3 31. Rb7 Kg8 32. Kf2 (32. Rxe7? Nb6 { Keeping black's knight trapped on a8 is more important than a free pawn. }) 32... Bf4 33. Kf3 (33. Bg3! { The only winning attempt according to Bronstein, but white missed black's 33rd move. }) 33... Rb8 34. Rxb8+ (34. Rxe7 Rb3 (34... g5! 35. Bf2 Rb3 36. Ne4 d2+ 37. Ke2 Rd3 38. Kd1 Nb6 { A terrifying line where black equalizes anyway. }) 35. Bxf6 $18 { [%csl Gc3] }) 34... Bxb8 35. Na4 Bd6 36. Bf2 Kf7 37. Ke3 (37. Bxc5 Bxc5 38. Nxc5 Nb6 $10 { The knight finally gets active. }) 37... Nc7 38. Kxd3 Na6 39. Ke4 f5+ 40. Kf3 e6 41. Nb6 $10 { Draw agreed } 1/2-1/2


