1. d4 Nf6 (1... d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Bg5 dxc4 5. e4 b5 (5... Nxe4)) 2. c4 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. e4 Nb6 7. Ne2 c5 8. d5 (8. dxc5 Qxd1+ 9. Kxd1 Na4 { [%cal Ga4c5] } 10. Nbc3 Nxc5) 8... e6 9. O-O O-O 10. a4 (10. Nbc3) 10... Na6 11. Na3 exd5 12. exd5 Bf5 { Diverging from the line that Euwe had published in 1950 as saying it was better for white } (12... Nb4 13. Nc3) 13. Nc3 (13. Bf4 Bxb2 { [%csl Gb1][%cal Gf5b1] } 14. Ra2 Bg7) 13... Nb4 { [%csl Gf4][%cal Gd5d6,Gb4c6] } 14. Be3 Rc8 { [%csl Gd3] } (14... Nd3 15. a5 Nd7 16. g4 { [%cal Gf5d3] } 16... Nxb2 { Black can get away with this, but doesn't attain the octopus knight they wanted. }) 15. d6 Bd3 (15... Nd3! 16. Bxb7 (16. Rb1 Qxd6) (16. Qd2 { [%cal Gd2b2,Gb6a4] } 16... Qxd6 17. a5 (17. Rfd1 c4 { [%cal Gg3g4,Gb2b3,Gf5g4,Gg4d1,Gg7a1] } 18. b3 cxb3 19. g4 { [%csl Gc3] }) 17... Na8 (17... Nd7 { [%cal Gd3b2] } 18. g4 Bxg4 19. Nc4) 18. g4) 16... Nxb2 { [%cal Gb2d1,Gg7c3,Gc8b8] } 17. Qb3 Rb8 18. Qxb2 Nxa4 $19 { [%csl Gb2,Gc3][%cal Gc3a4,Gb8b7] }) 16. Bxb7 (16. a5 { "Necessary" - Bronstein } 16... Bxf1 17. Kxf1 Nd7 18. Bxb7 Rb8 19. a6 { To secure the bishop deep in black's camp }) 16... Rb8 17. Bg2 Bxf1 18. Kxf1 Nd7 19. Nc4 Ne5 20. Nxe5 Bxe5 { [%cal Ge3c5] } 21. Bxc5 Qa5 { White has two pawns for the exchange. Interesting complications arise. } 22. Be3 Rfd8 23. Ne4 Bxd6 { [%cal Ga5a6,Ga6f1,Ga6d6] } 24. Nf6+ Kh8 (24... Kg7 { In one variation, the king needs to defend the f pawn }) 25. Bd4 Be5 { [%cal Ga5e5] } 26. Nd7 f6 (26... Rxd7 27. Bxe5+ Qxe5 28. Qxd7 Qxb2 29. Re1 { [%csl Gf7] } 29... Kg7 { If only our king was on g7 already! }) 27. Bxe5 fxe5 28. Qd2 (28. Qd6 Rb6 { [%cal Gd7b6,Gd8d6] } (28... Qa6+ 29. Qxa6 Nxa6 30. Nxb8 Rxb8 31. Re1 { Black would have been forced to give up the exchange and go for a bad endgame } { [%csl Ga4][%cal Gb8b2] } 31... Nc5 32. Rxe5 Nxa4 33. Ra5 Nxb2 34. Rxa7 { [%csl Gh8] } 34... Re8 35. Bf3 Nd3 { [%cal Gf3e2,Gf1e1,Ge1d2] } 36. h4 Re1+ 37. Kg2 Re8 38. Bd1 { [%csl Gh8][%cal Gh7h5] }) 29. Qe7! Nc6 30. Qf6+ Kg8 31. Rd1 $18 { [%cal Gg2d5] }) 28... Rbc8?! (28... Qa6+ 29. Kg1 Qe6! { [%cal Gd7b8,Gd7c5,Gd8d2,Gc5e6,Gd2b2] } 30. Nc5 Qb6 (30... Qe7 31. Qc3 Rdc8) (30... Rxd2 31. Nxe6 Rxb2 { [%cal Gb4d3,Gd3f2] })) 29. Kg1 Qc5 30. Bh3 (30. Nxc5 Rxd2 31. Ne4 Rxb2 $19) 30... Qe7 31. Qe2 Rxd7 32. Bxd7 Qxd7 33. Qxe5+ Kg8 { Black is up a piece, but must avoid exchanging queenside pawns, needs to find shelter for his king, an dbring his knight to the kingside to target the f2 pawn. } 34. Qe4 a5 35. h4 { [%cal Gh4h5] } 35... Qd5 36. Qg4 Rf8 37. Rd1 Qf3 38. Qc4+ Qf7 39. Qc5 Qf5 40. Qc4+ Qf7 41. Qc5 Qf5 42. Qc4+ Kg7 { [%cal Gb4c6,Gc6e5,Ge5g4,Gg4f2] } 43. Qd4+ Qf6 44. Qc5 Rf7 { [%cal Gf6f2] } 45. Rd2 Qe7 { [%cal Gc5a5,Ge7e1,Ge1d2] } 46. Qc3+ Rf6 47. Rd4 Nc6 48. Rd5 (48. Rf4 Qe5 49. Rxf6 Qxc3 50. Rxg6+ Kxg6 51. bxc3 { But this ending is lost anyway } 51... Ne5 52. Kf1 Kf5 53. Ke2 Ke4 54. h5 h6 { Zug }) 48... Qe6 49. Rc5 h5 50. b3 Kf7 51. Rb5 Qd7 52. Kg2 Qe7 53. Qc4+ Kg7 54. Qd3 Kh6 55. Rd5 Rf7 56. Rd6 Ne5 { [%cal Ge5g4,Gg4f2] } 57. Qe3+ Kh7 58. Rb6?? (58. Rd5 Rf5 59. Rxa5 (59. f3!! { The only way to stop any progress from black - deny the g4 square from the knight. }) 59... Qb7+ 60. f3 (60. Kh3 Qh1#) (60. Kh2 Nf3+ 61. Kg2 Nxh4+) 60... Nc4) 58... Qc7! { With Ng4 coming, black is completely winning. So white resigned, rather than allow the attack to continue unabated. } { [%cal Ge5g4] } (58... Ng4? 59. Qxe7 Rxe7 60. b4 { Some drawing chances for white }) 59. Rb5 (59. f3 Rxf3 $19) (59. Qe4) 59... Ng4 $19 0-1


