1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 d6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 g5 7. dxe5 (7. Bg3 e4 8. Nd2 e3 9. fxe3 { A dubious pawn sacrifice according to the computer, but one in which black gets all the fun. }) 7... gxh4 8. exf6 Qxf6 9. Nd5 Qxb2? { Extremely greedy } 10. Rb1 (10. Nxc7+ Kd8 11. Nxa8 d5!? 12. Qc1! { Forced if white wants to retain an advantage. } (12. Rc1?? Bb4+ 13. Nd2 Nc5 14. Rc2 Qe5 15. e3 Bf5 { A dream attacking position for black, even down a rook. })) 10... Qxa2 11. Nxc7+ Kd8 12. Nxa8 Nc5 { After this move, however, there is simply no attack. } (12... Bg7!? 13. Rc1 Qa3 14. e3 { Another forced move by white just to deal with the Bc3+ idea. } 14... Bc3+ 15. Ke2) 13. Ra1 Qb2 14. Qd4 Qxd4 15. Nxd4 Bg7 16. e3 Re8 17. Be2 Bxd4 18. exd4 Nb3 19. Rxa7 Nxd4 20. Ra2 h3 21. Rg1 Rg8 22. g4 $18 { Black resigned. } 1-0


