1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Nf3 Nc6 6. g3 c4 { After an eventual e4, the d pawn will become passed. Meanwhile the queenside majority is a bit slow to actually realize its potential if white is efficiently playing in the center. } 7. Bg2 Bb4 8. O-O Nge7 9. e4 dxe4 10. Nxe4 O-O 11. Qc2 $146 { A novelty at the time. } (11. a3 Ba5 12. Qa4 Bg4 $10) 11... Qd5 (11... Nxd4 12. Nxd4 Qxd4 13. Rd1 Qe5 14. Bf4 { White regains the pawn and a huge lead in development. }) 12. Be3 Ng6? (12... Bf5 13. Nh4! Nxd4 14. Bxd4 Qxd4 15. Nxf5 Nxf5 16. Rfd1 Qb6 (16... Qe5 17. Rd5 Qxd5 18. Nf6+ gxf6 19. Bxd5 $18) 17. a3 Ba5 18. Qxc4 $16) (12... Qh5 { If this is the best move, it means that black's entire setup needs work. Not only does this directly hang the c pawn, it looks like black's pieces are scattered throughout the board with no homes to call their own. }) 13. Nh4 { [%cal Gg6h4,Ge4f6] } (13. Nfg5 Bf5 14. g4 Bxe4 15. Nxe4 Qd7 16. Qxc4 $16 { [%cal Gd4d5] }) 13... Qb5 14. Nxg6 hxg6 15. a3 Be7 16. d5! Na5 17. d6 { Every move here builds on the initiative and doesn't give Stahlberg a second to regroup his pieces. } 17... Bd8 18. Nc3 Qa6 19. Rad1 Bg4 20. Rd4 Bf5 21. Qa4 Rb8 { [%cal Gb7b5] } 22. Rd5 (22. d7 b5 23. Qd1 $18 { [%cal Ge3c5,Gc5f8] }) 22... Be6 23. Re5 b6 24. d7 (24. Rxe6 fxe6 25. Qc2 { [%csl Gg6] } 25... Rf6 26. Bd4 Kh7 27. Be4 Rf5 28. g4! $18) 24... b5 25. Rxb5?? (25. Qd1! { With no time, Reshevsky doesn't find this move - always retreat }) 25... Rxb5 26. Qxb5 Qxb5 27. Nxb5 a6 (27... Bxd7! 28. Nxa7?? Bf6 { The knight is trapped on a7 more than it is a strength. Taking the pawn here is a mistake. }) 28. Nc3 Bxd7 29. Rd1 Bc8 { This forcing variation is good enough to win, but trading all the pieces means there is no hope for using the initiative to transition to a completely won game. } 30. Ne4 Be7 31. Bc5 Bxc5 32. Nxc5 Bf5 33. Nxa6 Re8 34. Bf3 Nb3 35. Kg2 Bc2 36. Rd7 Bf5 37. Rd1 Bc2 38. Rd7 Bf5 39. Rd6 Be6 40. Nc7 Re7 41. Nxe6 $18 { Black resigned, as the c pawn will soon fall, and the two passed queenside pawns are surely enough to win. } 1-0


