1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 c5 5. Bd3 d5 6. Nf3 O-O 7. O-O Nc6 8. a3 Bxc3 9. bxc3 dxc4 10. Bxc4 Qc7 11. Bd3 { [%cal Ge3e4] } (11. Bb2 e5 12. h3 Bf5 { A more respected line. However, it is still not so clear how the bishop on b2 will extricate itself from behind the pawn wall. }) 11... e5! { Making e4 hard to suggest. } 12. Qc2 Re8 13. e4 exd4 (13... c4! 14. Bxc4 exd4 15. cxd4 Na5 16. Bd3 Qxc2 17. Bxc2 Nxe4 $10) 14. cxd4 Bg4 (14... cxd4 15. e5 Nd5 16. Bxh7+ Kh8 { White has the initiative here. }) 15. Qxc5 (15. e5 Bxf3 16. exf6 Nxd4 17. Bxh7+ Kh8 18. fxg7+ Kxg7 19. Bb2 Rad8 { The line Euwe was tempting white to play, but it's arguably equal looking at 70 years of theory. }) 15... Nxe4 16. Bxe4 Rxe4 17. Ng5 Re7 (17... Rxd4 18. Bb2 Qf4 (18... Rd3! $10 { An extremely complicated exchange sacrifice }) (18... Rdd8)) 18. Qc2 { [%cal Gc2h7] } 18... g6 19. Ne4 Bf5 { [%cal Ge4f6,Gg8g7,Gg7f6] } 20. Nf6+ Kg7 21. Qd2! Kxf6 { [%cal Gc1b2,Gd2h6] } 22. d5 Rd8 23. Bb2+ (23. Qh6 Rxd5 24. Bb2+ Nd4 25. Rad1 Red7) (23. Qg5+ Kg7 24. dxc6 { [%cal Gc7c6,Gg5e7] } 24... f6 25. Qh6+ Kg8 26. cxb7 $10 { Best play according to the engine. Black returns the piece and pawn in order to get his king to safety. }) 23... Ne5 24. f4 Qc5+ 25. Kh1 (25. Bd4 Qxd5 26. Bxe5+ Rxe5 27. fxe5+ Kg7 $10 { Always sacrifice the exchange. }) 25... Rxd5 26. fxe5+ (26. Bxe5+ Rexe5 27. Qb2 Qb5 28. fxe5+ Rxe5 (28... Kg7 29. Qxb5 Rxb5 $10) 29. Qxb5 Rxb5 30. g4! $18) 26... Ke6 (26... Kg7 27. e6+ (27. Qg5 { [%cal Gg5e7] } 27... Re6 28. Rxf5 Qc2! $15 { [%cal Gc2f5,Gc2b2] }) 27... f6) 27. Qg5 Kd7 (27... Qc2?? 28. Rac1 Qxb2 29. Qf6+ Kd7 30. e6+ $18 { [%cal Gf6b2] }) 28. Rac1 Qb6 29. Bc3 { [%cal Gc3b4] } 29... Re8 30. Bb4 (30. h3! h5 { [%cal Gc3e1,Ge1g3] } 31. Be1 Qe6 { Even though there are so many ways white can attack, the sheer number of defenders stops this attack before it can begin. } (31... Rexe5 32. Bh4) 32. Bb4 Qxe5) 30... Rexe5 31. Qh4 a5 { [%cal Gh4h7,Ga5b4,Gh7f7] } 32. Be1 h5 33. Bf2 Qa6 34. Bg3 Re4 { [%cal Gh4g5,Gd7e6] } 35. Rxf5 Rxh4 36. Rxd5+ Ke6 { [%cal Ga6f1] } 37. Rcd1 (37. Re5+ Kf6 38. Rf1+?? { [%cal Gf1f6] } 38... Kg7 39. Bxh4 { If the queen wasn't looking at f1, this variation would have been nice. }) 37... Qc4 38. Rd6+ Ke7 39. Rd7+ Kf6 (39... Kf8 40. Rd8+ Kg7 41. Be5+ f6 42. R8d7+ Kh6 43. Bxf6 { Looks scary, but... } { [%cal Gd7d8,Gd8h8] } 43... Rf4! $19) 40. Bxh4+ Qxh4 41. Rf1+ Kg5 42. Rd5+ f5 43. Rxa5 $10 { Draw agreed. } 1/2-1/2


