1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 d6 3. Nf3 g6 4. g3 Bg7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O Nc6 7. Nc3 (7. d5!? Na5 8. Qa4 c5 $10) 7... Bg4 8. h3 (8. d5 Na5 9. Nd2 c5 10. Rb1 $14) 8... Bxf3 9. Bxf3 Nd7 10. Bg2 Nxd4 11. Bxb7 Rb8 12. Bg2 c5? { Black needed to keep the c5 square open for the knight, so that the b pawn can be poked at with a5-a4. Without the knight on c5, the pawn on a4 cannot be maintained, and so the pressure on the b file is imaginary. } 13. e3 Ne6 14. Qc2 a5 15. Bd2 Ne5 { There are simply no good plans for black because there are no weaknesses to target anymore. } 16. b3 Qd7 17. Kh2 Nc6 18. Rad1 Ned8 19. Be1 Kh8 20. Na4 Qc8 21. Bc3 Bxc3 22. Nxc3 Qf5 23. Qxf5 gxf5 24. Rd5 Ne6 25. Rxf5 Nb4 26. Rh5 Ng7 27. Rh4 Nf5 28. Rf4 e6 29. Rd1 Rb6 30. Na4 Rbb8 31. Be4 Ng7 32. Rxd6 Nxa2 33. Nxc5 $18 { Black resigned. } 1-0


